{
  "doc_id": "22149",
  "text": "Our findings indicate a significant direct relationship between overall taste function or bitter taste and PROP taster status in HC subjects, who displayed a similar trend also for the other qualities. These results are consistent with those revealing that healthy PROP super-taster subjects, compared to non-taster, possess a greater density of fungiform taste papillae that can explain their high general taste sensitivity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Differently, we have not found a specific effect of PROP taster status on taste function in IBD patients that may be explained by oral pathologies, especially those in the dorsal surface of tongue [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . This suggests that IBD patients who are PROP super-tasters do not have taste advantages over PROP non-tasters.",
